Package com.cafean.client.anim.available

Class JobAvailabilityQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.anim.available.JobAvailabilityQueue
  • public class JobAvailabilityQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    A Queue of jobs that are being checked to determine if they are available for animation.

      • addRequest

        public void addRequest​(java.lang.String jobLocation,
                       java.lang.String streamLocation,
                       PlatformDefinition platform,
                       java.io.File model,
                       boolean openImmediately,
                       java.lang.String[] dataSourceNames,
                       java.lang.String[] fileLabels)
        Requests that the given animation model MED be opened and connected to the given job on the given platform as soon as it is available.
        Parameters:
        jobLocation - the location of the animation job within a stream
        streamLocation - the location of the job stream.
        platform - the PlatformDefinition defining the platform on which the job is being executed
        model - the File that should be opened to animate the given job
        openImmediately - the flag that indicates the animation should open as soon as the plot data is available.
        dataSourceNames - the names for locating the data sources in the file that should connect to this job.
        fileLabels - the String[] containing plot files in the job stream to load..
